    • Method Detail

      • authenticate

        public OrderResponse authenticate(String personalIdentityNumber,
                                  String endUserIp,
                                  Requirement requirement)
                           throws BankIDException
        Request an authentication order. The BankIDClient.collect(String) method is used to query the status of the order.
        Specified by:
        authenticate in interface BankIDClient
        Parameters:
        personalIdentityNumber - the ID number of the user trying to be authenticated (optional). If the ID number is omitted the user must use the same device and the client must be started with the autoStartToken returned in orderResponse
        endUserIp - the user IP address as seen by the relying party
        requirement - used by the relying party to set requirements how the authentication or sign operation must be performed. Default rules are applied if omitted
        Returns:
        an order response
        Throws:
        BankIDException - for errors
